## Code Standards

- Follow Django best practices
- Use semantic HTML
- Write accessible code (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)
- Optimize for performance (lazy loading, caching)
- Use modern CSS (Flexbox, Grid)
- Follow responsive design principles

## UI/UX Guidelines

- Maintain consistent design language
- Use dark theme by default (trading dashboards)
- Ensure fast load times
- Provide clear error messages
- Show loading states for async operations
- Make data tables sortable and filterable

## Data Visualization

- Use TradingView Lightweight Charts for candlestick charts
- Display indicators (EMA, SMA, MACD) as overlay lines
- Show buy/sell signals as markers
- Provide zoom and pan capabilities
- Include time range selectors

